    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Saddle Point [S+N]\n\nWhen eigenvalues are real with opposite signs, trajectories approach the origin along the stable eigenvector and diverge along the unstable eigenvector. The fixed point is unstable.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Saddle point: eigenvalues of opposite sign */\nA_saddle : matrix([1, 0], [0, -2])$\nevals_saddle : eigenvalues(A_saddle);\n\nprint(\"Eigenvalues:\", evals_saddle[1])$\nprint(\"One positive, one negative => saddle point\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 109,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "[[-2,1],[1,1]]\nEigenvalues: [-2,1]\nOne positive, one negative => saddle point"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Saddle point phase portrait: hyperbolic trajectories */\nax_draw2d(\n  ax_vector_field(x, -2*y, x, -3, 3, y, -3, 3),\n  ax_streamline(x, -2*y, x, -3, 3, y, -3, 3),\n  title=\"Saddle Point\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\",\n  aspect_ratio=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 110,
      "outputs": [
