    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Stable Spiral [S+N]\n\nWhen eigenvalues are complex conjugates with negative real part, trajectories spiral inward toward the origin. The imaginary part determines the rotation frequency.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Stable spiral: complex eigenvalues with negative real part */\nA_spiral : matrix([-1, 2], [-2, -1])$\nevals_spiral : eigenvalues(A_spiral);\n\nprint(\"Eigenvalues:\", evals_spiral[1])$\nprint(\"Complex with Re < 0 => stable spiral\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 111,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "[[-(2*%i)-1,2*%i-1],[1,1]]\nEigenvalues: [-(2*%i)-1,2*%i-1]\nComplex with Re < 0 => stable spiral"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Stable spiral: trajectories wind inward */\nax_draw2d(\n  ax_vector_field(-x + 2*y, -2*x - y, x, -3, 3, y, -3, 3),\n  ax_streamline(-x + 2*y, -2*x - y, x, -3, 3, y, -3, 3),\n  title=\"Stable Spiral\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\",\n  aspect_ratio=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 112,
      "outputs": [
