    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Centre\n\nThe simple harmonic oscillator $\\dot{x} = y$, $\\dot{y} = -x$ has pure imaginary eigenvalues. Trajectories form closed orbits -- neither converging nor diverging.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Centre: pure imaginary eigenvalues */\nA_centre : matrix([0, 1], [-1, 0])$\nevals_centre : eigenvalues(A_centre);\n\nprint(\"Eigenvalues:\", evals_centre[1])$\nprint(\"Pure imaginary => centre (closed orbits)\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 115,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "[[-%i,%i],[1,1]]\nEigenvalues: [-%i,%i]\nPure imaginary => centre (closed orbits)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Centre: closed circular orbits */\nax_draw2d(\n  ax_vector_field(y, -x, x, -3, 3, y, -3, 3),\n  ax_streamline(y, -x, x, -3, 3, y, -3, 3),\n  title=\"Centre (Simple Harmonic Oscillator)\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\",\n  aspect_ratio=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 116,
      "outputs": [
        {
